comments.body:
I have been able to reproduce this by unpublishing and trying to republish issue 17 in production.  The issue is successfully unpublished but triggers a 500 error in the browser, and the issue can be republished successfully, but the articles are not visible in the issue.

Here is the error from Apache:

```log
[Thu Apr 27 18:24:22.427032 2023] [php7:error] [pid 31124] [client 128.112.203.144:39742] PHP Fatal error:  Uncaught PDOException: SQLSTATE[42P10]: Invalid column reference: 7 ERROR:  there is no unique or exclusion constraint matching the ON CONFLICT specification in /var/www/ojs-3.3.0-8/lib/pkp/lib/vendor/doctrine/dbal/lib/Doctrine/DBAL/Driver/PDOStatement.php:115\n
Stack trace:\n
#0 /var/www/ojs-3.3.0-8/lib/pkp/lib/vendor/doctrine/dbal/lib/Doctrine/DBAL/Driver/PDOStatement.php(115): PDOStatement->execute()\n
#1 /var/www/ojs-3.3.0-8/lib/pkp/lib/vendor/laravel/framework/src/Illuminate/Database/Connection.php(489): Doctrine\\DBAL\\Driver\\PDOStatement->execute()\n
#2 /var/www/ojs-3.3.0-8/lib/pkp/lib/vendor/laravel/framework/src/Illuminate/Database/Connection.php(664): Illuminate\\Database\\Connection->Illuminate\\Database\\{closure}()\n
#3 /var/www/ojs-3.3.0-8/lib/pkp/lib/vendor/laravel/framework/src/Illuminate/Database/Connection.php(631): Illuminate\\Database\\Connection->runQueryCallback()\n
#4 /var/www/ojs-3.3.0-8/lib/pkp/lib/vendor/laravel/framework/src/Illuminate/Database/Connection.php(496): Illuminate\\Database\\Connection->run() in /var/www/ojs-3.3.0-8/lib/pkp/lib/vendor/laravel/framework/src/Illuminate/Database/Connection.php on line 671, referer: https://openpublishing.princeton.edu/index.php/pjpf/manageIssues
```
This appears to be the same or a similar issue - https://forum.pkp.sfu.ca/t/invalid-column-reference-7-error-there-is-no-unique-or-exclusion-constraint-matching-the-on-conflict-specification/70199

Applying [this patch](https://github.com/pkp/ojs/commit/a376551cc031d9fb55f56e20e7de2240bb268cdc#diff-3eeee96f737c976403c06aea886c4c5ceabbfd87714a7dea41836e6c6659c241) manually addressed the issue in production.  I was able to successfully unpublish/publish Issue 17 and 16 (both of which would not publish before) and unpublish/republish issue 27 (which was functioning normally already). 

It appears this code has been updated in OJS 3.3.0-14; we are currently running OJS 3.3.0-8 in staging and production.  I will next attempt to recreate this issue in OJS 3.3.0-8 on staging and apply a fix to the playbook in princeton_ansible, then test on staging.

orangelight.title: Display Basic Request form for items that have more than 500? number of holdings
Request form Cannot Load Holdings that have many items

comments.body:
To get a sense of the scale of the issue we are facing here asked for some fresh data on holdings with many items:

https://github.com/PrincetonUniversityLibrary/alma-config/issues/456

Update: Approximately 2,700 holdings have greater than 100 items. 68 greater than 1000, 202 greater than 500.

Hello we discussed this at our weekly check-in for OL issues today. There is a prospect to bring bibliographic level data for the constituent records into the Aeon request.  

So I think we could extract following fields reliably: ItemAuthor, ItemTitle, ItemSubTitle, ItemDate, ItemEdition, ItemISxN, ReferenceNumber. 

I'm not sure how we'd extract the other data from a constituent record the values for ItemVolume, ItemIssue, ItemPages, ItemNumber since those are at the holding or item level data which only exist under a host record. I'm not exactly sure what ItemCitation is in this context.

Possible Implementation:

Constituent records like  99122598533506421 have a a data attribute attached to the html div with an id value of main-content:

data-host-id='["99125092613506421"]'

Currently we use this value as the mms ID to utilize when making an availability call to get the holding and item availability status of the host record from Alma. We could also use this to possible create a hash of constituent bibliographic level parameters taken from the solr document to pass over to the request form that can be used to override values from the host record that would otherwise be submitted to another system like Aeon.
